{"key":"processedPost-11515384","value":{"id":11515384,"first":11510801,"last":11517014,"when":1259041143,"utime":"11/24/09 07:39 AM","content":"The grain is the most nutritious part of the substrate.&nbsp; As I said, there's a point of diminishing returns when using higher and higher spawn rates.&nbsp; The point is a higher spawn rate will generally give more fruits than a lower one.&nbsp; That doesn't necessarily make a 1:1 ratio better.&nbsp; As said, spread that grain spawn, which is the most expensive part of the substrate, among more projects and you get more mushrooms for your buck.<br />RR","title":"Re: Question about higher spawn rate","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}